parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Rust on brake rotors can cause the brakes to fail, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: brake pedal feels soft or spongy.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: ABS failure can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: brake pedal goes to the floor

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: ABS sensor failure can cause the ABS system to malfunction, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: sensors need to be replaced or cleaned repeatedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Corrosion of Brake Lines and Components
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Corrosion of brake lines and components can cause brake fluid leakage, leading to a loss of brake power, increased stopping distances, and potentially accidents.
symptoms: inability to use the emergency brake

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Intermittent Failure of Power Brakes and Power Steering
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Intermittent failure of power brakes and power steering can cause unexpected loss of braking and steering assist, leading to increased stopping distances and difficulty controlling the vehicle, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Power brakes and power steering fail
but return to normal operation after restarting the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Corrosion around the cross member that supports the fuel tank can cause the fuel tank to become dislodged, leading to fuel leaks, fires, and potentially serious accidents.
symptoms: Visible corrosion around the cross member
rust or flaking metal around the fuel tank support
fuel tank sagging or hanging low
